{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:exodus.40",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "exodus",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Exodus 40 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:1",
      "text": "And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:2",
      "text": "The first month, the first day of the month, thou shalt set up the tabernacle of the testimony,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:3",
      "text": "And shalt put the ark in it, and shalt let down the veil before it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:4",
      "text": "And thou shalt bring in the table, and set upon it the things that are commanded according to the rite. The candlestick shall stand with its lamps,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:5",
      "text": "And the altar of gold, whereon the incense is burnt before the ark of the testimony. Thou shalt put the hanging in the entry of the tabernacle,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:6",
      "text": "And before it the altar of holocaust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:7",
      "text": "The laver between the altar and the tabernacle, and thou shalt fill it with water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:8",
      "text": "And thou shalt encompass the court with hangings, and the entry thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:9",
      "text": "And thou shalt take the oil of unction and anoint the tabernacle with its vessels, that they may be sanctified:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:10",
      "text": "The altar of holocaust and all its vessels:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:11",
      "text": "The laver with its foot: thou shalt consecrate all with the oil of unction, that they may be most holy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:12",
      "text": "And thou shalt bring Aaron and his sons to the door of the tabernacle of the testimony, and having washed them with water,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:13",
      "text": "Thou shalt put on them the holy vestments, that they may minister to me, and that the unction of them may prosper to an everlasting priesthood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:14",
      "text": "And Moses did all that the Lord had commanded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:15",
      "text": "So in the first month of the second year, the first day of the month, the tabernacle was set up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:16",
      "text": "And Moses reared it up, and placed the boards and the sockets and the bars, and set up the pillars,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:17",
      "text": "And spread the roof over the tabernacle, putting over it a cover, as the Lord had commanded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:18",
      "text": "And he put the testimony in the ark, thrusting bars underneath, and the oracle above.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:19",
      "text": "And when he had brought the ark into the tabernacle, he drew the veil before it to fulfil the commandment of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:20",
      "text": "And he set the table in the tabernacle of the testimony, at the north side, without the veil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:21",
      "text": "Setting there in order the loaves of proposition, as the Lord had commanded Moses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:22",
      "text": "He set the candlestick also in the tabernacle of the testimony, over against the table on the south side,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:23",
      "text": "Placing the lamps in order, according to the precept of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:24",
      "text": "He set also the altar of gold under the roof of the testimony, over against the veil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:25",
      "text": "And burnt upon it the incense of spices, as the Lord had commanded Moses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:26",
      "text": "And he put also the hanging in the entry of the tabernacle of the testimony,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:27",
      "text": "And the altar of holocaust in the entry of the testimony, offering the holocaust, and the sacrifices upon it, as the Lord had commanded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:28",
      "text": "And he set the laver between the tabernacle of the testimony and the altar, filling it with water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:29",
      "text": "And Moses and Aaron, and his sons, washed their hands and feet,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:30",
      "text": "When they went into the tabernacle of the covenant, and went to the altar, as the Lord had commanded Moses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:31",
      "text": "He set up also the court round about the tabernacle and the altar, drawing the hanging in the entry thereof. After all things were perfected,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:32",
      "text": "The cloud covered the tabernacle of the testimony, and the glory of the Lord filled it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:33",
      "text": "Neither could Moses go into the tabernacle of the covenant, the cloud covering all things, and the majesty of the Lord shining, for the cloud had covered all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:34",
      "text": "If at any time the cloud removed from the tabernacle, the children of Israel went forward by their troops:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:35",
      "text": "If it hung over, they remained in the same place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:exodus.40.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "exodus",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Exodus 40:36",
      "text": "For the cloud of the Lord hung over the tabernacle by day, and a fire by night, in the sight of all the children of Israel throughout all their mansions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
